nts1.n: THE NTS BREAKFAST SHOW W/ FLO
nts1.d: Breakfast, in Flo motion - served by Flo Dill, every Monday to Thursday.
Low, slow and sleazy sounds with babyschön, in the studio for the early afternoon shift…

nts1.n: DANCE MUSIC SHOW W/ BELL TOWERS
nts1.d:
Prolific producer + DJ from Melbourne, Australia - Bell Towers presents his Dance Music Show.
From the host: "No dance music - chill, cosy, sometimes introspective music for these cold winter days"

nts1.n: RHYTHM CONNECTION: The Year In Pumpers
nts1.d: A monthly journey into H.O.U.S.E. hosted by Dan Beaumont & Nadia Ksaiba featuring interviews & mixes from super special guests. Expect two hours of old bangers and upfront pumpers.
Tune in, turn on, clock out. Sofie K brings sleazy synthpop, pumping proto-house and campy club cuts to the NTS studio once a month.

nts1.n: Chicken Foot Soup w/ Goya Gumbani, Dom P & Morriarchi
nts1.d: London-based jazz artist Goya Gumbani stops by to share heartfelt picks from his collection.

London poet, artist and musician Nadeem Din-Gabisi traverses the themes and inspirations behind his debut album OFFSHORE, a project exploring his relationship to England, and his sense of belonging and identity.

North London native and Hyperdub signee Loraine James is an electronic producer who effortlessly blends Electronica and IDM with whispers of jazz and ambience all wrapped up in the artists key avant-garde aesthetic and sensibility.
From the host: "My 30th birthday playlist. a collection of songs I love that came out in 1995."

Drum & bass and jungle every month with Equinox & Dev/Null.
From the host: "Equinox & Dev/Null return with the last DRUM POETRY of the year, featuring an hour of new and exclusive hardcore/jungle"

Few other labels can lay claim to such a foundational role in the origin myth of house music as Chicago's Trax Records. 
Home to, and often introducing us to, artists like Frankie Knuckles, Joe Smooth, Armando, Phuture, Marshall Jefferson, Ron Hardy, Larry Heard and many more. Trax laid the sonic foundation of jacking rhythm tracks with a distinct disco feel. The formula remains much the same to this day.
NTS selects two hours of Trax classics and deep cuts.
Japanese DJ Yuka Mizuhara joins us for an hour every month, selecting the most feel good classic house and disco. Dig!

nts2.d: The sounds of the rap abyss and beyond, presented by the music blog No Bells. Hosted by Mano Sundaresan with special guests.

Themed mixes, hidden gems, bedroom demos, interviews and other odds and ends once a month. Email: animalimagesearch@gmail.com
From the host: "A selection of music by American composer Henry Flynt"
Edinburgh based party and reissue label present rarities and classics every month.
Explorations in music from Ruth Tafébé a.k.a The Afrosoulmessenger.

Selections from Ruby Khaira, long time record collector with a love of all things Punjabi music. Digging deep into the record crates as a celebration of Punjab's rich musical heritage and worldwide impact. From dance floor Bhangra bangers to desi folk anthems — if it was pressed onto vinyl, it might just get played.
From the host: "DesiVinyl is a journey through the rare grooves and forgotten treasures of Punjabi music released only on vinyl. It’s about the crackle of the needle, the worn album covers and the voices that carries generations of music lovers. From folk anthems that shook dance floors to tracks played on repeat."

Alessio Natalizia is Not Waving. Take the plunge with his monthly hour of fucked-up left techno, leftfield electronics, brain-twisting oddball pop and post-punk, dub offshoots and other diversions. 
ecstaticrecordings.com

nts2.n: POSH ISOLATION'S COPENHAGEN REPORT w/ Aria & Laura
nts2.d:
Danish label Posh Isolation join us for an hour a month.
From the host: "Reporting from Copenhagen, Aria and Laura invite you into a surreal sonic journey moving between formation and dissolution. A mix tracing the past year and the tension between a world in crisis and the intimate, fragile and luminous moments of being human."

Get in your feelings with Brussels party starters HE4RTBROKEN - the beloved Belgian collective that aren't scared of a few tears on the dance floor. Resident djs Liyo, Steff, Munix and ssaliva explore the full range of cathartic music listening together with some kindred-spirited emotive guests.
From the host: "Redstarstill  presents a nostalgic sound collage. Inspired by Since I Left You-era sampling logic, the set drifts between memory and mediation, where the real and the virtual blur into one continuous emotional space."

nts2.n: UNITED IN FLAMES W/ ULTRA CARO & MALIBU
nts2.d:
Malibu is a French electronic musician whose work sails between ambient and ethereal music.
Forever inspired by soft reverbed vocals and melodious chord progressions, Malibu’s music is an immersive nostalgic journey in a sea of synthetic strings and choirs.

nts2.n: Temporal Cove w/ LUCY (Cooper B. Handy)
nts2.d:
Where the wall meets the floor, Temporal Cove is a body of sound exploring the ethereal and ephemeral. Smilegoth dives into shoegaze, post-rock, house and more to articulate a flow of reverberations that can be felt on every surface.
From the host: _"Cooper B. Handy, known in music as LUCY, is a prolific, experimental American musician, singer, and producer from Cape Cod, recognized for his raw, homemade pop music, Style, and captivating live shows in the underground scene. Based in Western Massachusetts, he self-releases music and videos, using GarageBand, blending experimental sounds with conversational, honest lyrics, gaining a cult following for his prolific output across projects including Taxidermists, Club Casualties, and Safe Mind." _
Sematary (fka Grave Man), a key figure in cult new wave drill and horrorcore collective Haunted Mound presents his monthly NTS Show.
Glyn Maier, the mastermind behind sustainably minded label enmossed, selects some current favourites for an NTS guest show.

nts2.n: The 100% Music Hour w/ Nina Protocol
nts2.d: Nina Protocol, the artist-first music and streaming platform, hijack the NTS airwaves to play some of their team’s 2025 office anthems. All killer, no filler.

subtle.d: With a monthly show on Subtle, Niceup is a London based DJ with a unique style. Pushing UKG, Breakbeat, Bass, Electro and 140. Weaving through genres showcasing new releases and older cuts.

Jedah started DJ'ing at the tender age of 18 years of age specialising in UK Garage/Grime. 

Jedah is currently the DJ for Grime Original Hollowman Jendor of the former Grime Collective Essentials/ OG's.

Responsible for “that massive grime tune with the Psycho strings”, UK producers/DJs Trends & Boylan are well versed in what the scene has to offer. They use this platform to showcase music from across the 140 spectrum from Grime to Dubstep. Anything goes!!

XOSÉ is a DJ and aspiring producer mixing and making mostly UK Garage, Grime and UK Funky. FORWARD PRESSURE largely focuses on the aforementioned UK born genres, though you can expect a variety of UK influenced sounds.

Sempra is a producer & DJ based in London, specialising in the fusion of UK Garage, Jungle and Breakbeat with dreamy vocal melodies and the beautiful instrumentation found in Soul and contemporary RnB. Sempra’s consistent output has been released by labels such as Future Classic and Headroom, gaining industry support from the likes of Nia Archives, Sherelle, Yung Singh and Dr Dubplate.

Cicely is a northern raised London based music photographer and DJ. From learning to mix during lockdown, she has since played at clubs across the country in venues such as Fabric, Corsica and Fold.

Cicely runs a collective and events night under the name NRG CRU which focus heavily on the high energy rave sound. She is highly influenced by the northern sound she grew up with, and you can hear this within her sets. Expect heavy blends of techno and hardcore while she shines the light on her favourite northern artists.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Bristol-born and London-based, Not Bad For A Girl resident DaiSu has been involved in the music scene since 2018 and has featured on stations such as Radio 1 Dance, BBC 6 Music and Melodic Distraction, as well as playing on line ups for Keep Hush, Skiddle and Red Bull. Her penchant for bass, breaks and 2-step has landed her gigs supporting acts such as Interplanetary Criminal, Main Phase, Craigie Knowes and Big Ang. In September 2022, her debut EP ‘Lightwork’ was released with Gather Records and was featured in DJ Mag's staff picks that same month.

Vinyl DJ from Leigh-on-Sea. Loves collecting records with a wide array of taste ranging from House and Techno to Grime, Dubstep and Jungle. Garage holds a special place in his heart and makes up the largest part of my collection and DJ sets.

DJ & Producer hailing from Watford influenced by Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Grime with releases on NSX records & Ghost Phone, spinning electronic genres from R&B edits, Drum and Bass and everything in between.
Highlander brings you 2 hours of the freshest Jungle, Hardcore, Dubstep and Breaks. 3rd Saturday 7-9pm lock in!

subtle.n: What's The Weather, Selecta? w/ Megan Wroe

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

Wheel2Wheel is a Manchester based event which primarily focuses on the underground sectors to genres such as UK Garage, House, Tech House, Electro, Minimal and Breakbeat. Co-Founder Freddie SJ hosts the first hour of the show, sharing his favourites as well as recent digs across the genres, and then invites fellow friends, artists and nights from the scene to present hour-long guest mixes which aims to shine a light on their sound and who they are!


With hours of Discogs screen-time under his belt and a passion for 90's & early 00's releases, expect to hear a variety of different tunes from Labels you may have never heard of and Countries you might not expect!


Give us a follow on Instagram to hear about our upcoming events and all other things music related! @wheel2wheel.mcr

subtle.n: The Ice Box Sessions with Frigid

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

dublab.n: Daddy Differently and Dirty Dave - Things of Life
dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
